node.text: You will get to see it all on @peacocktv and @wwenetwork tonight at 5pm PST. It’s an incredible honor to be apart of the WWE Hall of Fame Class of 2020. To be apart of so many iconic WWE Superstars. I’ll be spamming you all later because I have so many people to thank, who have been apart of this incredible, memorable, historic journey.  This doesn’t mean the end, just a reflection of the past, a celebration of achievements, honors and barriers broken, and a beginning of a new chapter in an era where Mom’s are totally kicking ass! In our home that we call WWE we get to wear many masks. No matter my next one, in ring or out, it will always remain Fearless and with my ICONIC BELLA ARMY. Like us Bellas and the Bella Army have said from the beginning, We Run It, We Rule It and Haters Gonna Hate, Bellas Gonna Ball. Excited to share tonight with you all!! And even more excited that there will be more women competing at WrestleMania! We should never doubt the presence of women on the card, RAW, SmackDown, or PPV’s. Those days are done. Let’s do better. Let’s keep the equality going. We need and WANT more women matches and stories! And remember WWE Universe you are a huge part of that! Keep supporting women’s wrestling! Love you all!

node.text: minutes to watch. Also, please share it on your platforms too. I don’t know about you but this pandemic has definitely changed me. It has definitely been “The Great Realization” I needed. I’m looking at life so differently. What’s truly important to me. What I truly want to do with my time that I’m so grateful to have. Appreciating Mother Nature more in so many different ways. Living more simple. Truly putting my soon to be family first, even before a career I have made. Having more FaceTime and conversations with my loved ones that I miss. And truly giving my undivided attention to the ones that I sit with. Being picky about the people that surround me. Do they bring me joy, positivity and glee? I found this video so perfectly said and true. I hope we, as a world, do change after this and become renewed. And when we get opportunities to help with change we remember this time we all had to go through. We all remember how beautiful Mother Nature grew. We remember that we were in it together, even with different views. And we still help out the people less fortunate than us and still clap to say thank you. I truly hope after this, as a world, we don’t go back to our old ways. We remember what has happened and the hope for better days. I can definitely say that once we heal, it makes me excited, to experience a world so new with all of you. ❤️🌎🦋✨ @probablytomfoolery

node.text: Enjoyed a #sistersunday at @delectuswinery winery. 👯‍♀️ If your eyes love a good view and your palate craves a great full body red, especially Cabernets, this definitely needs to be on your wine tasting stop.🍷🍇💋 Love you @thebriebella !! Much needed Mama’s day!! ❤️

node.text: Loved this moment from last Sunday 🥰 I think Teo prefers Mama with no makeup lol and only one person saying his name! Ha Aww my precious Tey Tey! And Dada we miss you soooo much! We are excited and so proud of you for your big premiere tomorrow night!! ❤️

node.text: Today starts Hispanic Heritage Month and tomorrow is Mexican Independence Day! ❤️🤍💚🇲🇽 I’m so grateful for my hispanic roots, my family, my ancestors, being raised in Mexican traditions and honoring the history of the Hispanic people. ✨ Our hopes is that Matteo will be trilingual and speak Spanish, Russian and English. I’ll have to learn more with him! lol Bri and I have always tried to bring our Latin side into whatever we do whether it’s the ring, filming or within our companies. 🌹 Always have been so proud to be a Latina! 💃🏽Love you Garcia family!! Love you Dad!! @jegarcia64 Thank you for always showing us where our family is from and how we got here. “Uno no elige a su familia. Son un regalo de Dios para ti, como tú eres para ellos.” Un día finalmente seré fluida en español lol Te amo Bella Army!! #hispanicheritagemonth #mexicanindependenceday

node.text: BRB as I go and cry my eyes out! 😭 So proud of this little one!! For almost a week now Teo has been walking more and more! I can’t believe how quick this happens! I have admired his tenacity and persistence, crazy how our little ones can inspire us. 🥰 Oh Teo welcome to another milestone my love. ❤️

node.text: So proud of my Love @theartemc !!! He didn’t win but goodness forever and always he will be an Emmy nominated choreographer, what a dream!! So well deserved! I felt so special being his date tonight and watching my Love sparkle!! Goodness he’s so talented! Love you Click!!! And congrats @derekhough you are so talented as well as you @hayley.erbert two gorgeous people inside and out!! But watch out next year Derek ;) I got a man on a mission lol Oh and thank you @nataliesaidi for styling us! Here’s to more styling events together!😍❤️‍🔥

node.text:
So I had a dream that when I hit 10 million followers I want @theartemc to pull me in a winery, play Selena Gomez & Rauw Alejandro, drink champagne, salsa dance with me, and make another baby lol Well we did just that… except for the baby making part!😜 Love all 10 million of you! Grateful for you. 🤍✨ Thank you for joining this wild journey with me! 🤗💋😘 #bellaarmy 

Filmed by: @rjmckinnon 
Produced by: @rjmckinnon @theartemc 
Choreographed by: @theartemc 
Skirt by: @sorapollondon 💃🏽 @nataliesaidi 
Winery: @hillfamilyestate 
I do not own this music. But goodness do I love me some @selenagomez and @rauwalejandro This is such a sexy, passionate song. Lyrics make you feel something y quiero bailar sexy y apasionadamente. ❤️‍🔥
